body:
I am testing on the latest develop branch, EllisLab-CodeIgniter-v2.1.0-3113-g082aa40.zip

Example 1:

```
$name = get_instance()->db
    ->select('name')
    ->from('products')
    ->where('id', 132)
    ->get()
    ->row('name')
;

var_dump($name);
```

Example 2:

```
$name = get_instance()->db
    ->select('name')
    ->from('products')
    ->where('id', 132)
    ->get()
    ->row()
    ->name
;

var_dump($name);
```

Both of the examples are equivalent and the return the desired string value.

When the table is empty or a record with the targeted id does not exist, then
no recordset is returned. In this case both examples return NULL which I think
is the correct behavior.

But also messages appear:

```
For Example 1:

A PHP Error was encountered
Severity: Warning
Message: array_key_exists() expects parameter 2 to be array, null given
Filename: database/DB_result.php
Line Number: 276

For Example 2:

A PHP Error was encountered
Severity: Notice
Message: Trying to get property of non-object
```

I think these messages should be supressed. Here is a quick workaround about Example 1:

```
class CI_DB_result {

...
...
...


    public function row($n = 0, $type = 'object')
    {
        if ( ! is_numeric($n))
        {
            // We cache the row data for subsequent uses
            if ( ! is_array($this->row_data))
            {
                $this->row_data = $this->row_array(0);
            }

            // ---------------------------------- This is the patch for Example 1.
            if ( ! is_array($this->row_data))
            {
                return NULL;
            }
            //----------------------------------- End of the patch.

            // array_key_exists() instead of isset() to allow for MySQL NULL values
            if (array_key_exists($n, $this->row_data))
            {
                return $this->row_data[$n];
            }
            // reset the $n variable if the result was not achieved
            $n = 0;
        }

        if ($type === 'object') return $this->row_object($n);
        elseif ($type === 'array') return $this->row_array($n);
        else return $this->custom_row_object($n, $type);
    }


...
...
...
}
```
